dcterms:description: A massive collection of small molecules docked into cognate and non-cognate receptors. It includes 18,450 bound protein-ligand crystal structures clustered by pocket similarity, which were used for a combinatorial docking procedure to increase training data and capture the distribution of structures typically used in drug discovery.
dcterms:title: CrossDocked2020
